{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about the current capabilities of OpenUSD in Swift"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OpenUSD in Swift is currently evolving and may change in the future. Here are some key features currently supported:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Reference-types-in-Swift","level":3,"text":"Reference types in Swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"UsdStage and SdfLayer are imported as classes in Swift and behave like classes written in Swift. When Swift passes a raw pointer to UsdStage or SdfLayer, Swift automatically increments or decrements the underlying reference count as needed, allowing Swift or C++ to influence the lifetime of the same UsdStage or SdfLayer."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["func makeTempStage() -> pxr.UsdStage {","    return Overlay.Dereference(pxr.UsdStage.CreateNew(\"\/tmp\/myStage.usda\", .LoadAll))","}","","func defineXform(_ stage: pxr.UsdStage, _ path: pxr.SdfPath) {","    stage.DefinePrim(path, .UsdGeomTokens.Xform)","}","","let stage = makeTempStage()","defineXform(stage, \"\/hello\")","let layer = Overlay.Dereference(stage.GetRootLayer())","layer.Save(false)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftUsd\/documentation\/SwiftUsd\/WhatIsAForeignReferenceType","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftUsd\/documentation\/SwiftUsd\/ForeignReferenceTypesAndSmartPointers","isActive":true},{"text":" for more information.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When working in Swift, do not use "},{"code":"TfRefPtr.pointee","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"TfWeakPtr.pointee","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"t